#: ../../source/info/social.rst:2
msgid "社会工程学"
msgstr "Social Engineering"

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:5
msgid "企业信息收集"
msgstr "Enterprise Information Gathering"

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:6
msgid "一些网站如天眼查等，可以提供企业关系挖掘、工商信息、商标专利、企业年报等信息查询，可以提供企业的较为细致的信息。"
msgstr ""
"Some websites, such as Tianyancha, provide queries for corporate "
"relationships, business registration information, trademarks and patents, "
"annual reports, and other data. They can provide fairly detailed information "
"about an enterprise."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:8
msgid "公司主站中会有业务方向、合作单位等信息。"
msgstr "A company's main website may contain information such as business directions and partner organizations."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:11
msgid "人员信息收集"
msgstr "Personnel Information Gathering"

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:12
msgid "针对人员的信息收集考虑对目标重要人员、组织架构、社会关系的收集和分析。其中重要人员主要指高管、系统管理员、开发、运维、财务、人事、业务人员的个人电脑。"
msgstr ""
"Personnel-focused information gathering involves collecting and analyzing "
"information about key target personnel, organizational structure, and social "
"relationships. Key personnel mainly include executives, system "
"administrators, developers, operations staff, finance staff, HR staff, and "
"business personnel, as well as their personal computers."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:14
msgid "人员信息收集较容易的入口点是网站，网站中可能包含网站的开发、管理维护等人员的信息。从网站联系功能中和代码的注释信息中都可能得到的所有开发及维护人员的姓名和邮件地址及其他联系方式。"
msgstr ""
"A relatively easy entry point for personnel information gathering is the "
"website itself, which may contain information about developers, administrators,"
" and maintainers. Contact functions and code comments may reveal names, email"
" addresses, and other contact details for development and maintenance staff."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:16
msgid "在获取这些信息后，可以在Github/Linkedin等社交、招聘网站中进一步查找这些人在互联网上发布的与目标站点有关的一切信息，分析并发现有用的信息。"
msgstr ""
"After obtaining this information, continue searching on social and recruiting"
" platforms such as GitHub and LinkedIn for any target-related information "
"published by these people, then analyze it for useful findings."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:18
msgid "此外，可以对获取到的邮箱进行密码爆破的操作，获取对应的密码。"
msgstr "In addition, the collected email addresses can be used for password brute forcing to obtain corresponding passwords."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:21
msgid "钓鱼"
msgstr "Phishing"

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:22
msgid "基于之前收集到的信息，可以使用Office/CHM/RAR/EXE/快捷方式等文件格式制作钓鱼邮件发送至目标，进一步收集信息。"
msgstr ""
"Based on previously collected information, phishing emails can be crafted "
"using file formats such as Office, CHM, RAR, EXE, and shortcuts, then sent to"
" the target for further information gathering."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:24
msgid "其中Office可以使用Office漏洞、宏、OLE对象、PPSX等方式构造利用文件。"
msgstr "Office exploit documents can be built using Office vulnerabilities, macros, OLE objects, PPSX, and similar techniques."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:26
msgid "Exe可以使用特殊的Unicode控制字符如RLO (Right-to-Left Override) 等来构建容易混淆的文件名。"
msgstr ""
"EXE files can use special Unicode control characters such as RLO "
"(Right-to-Left Override) to create confusing file names."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:28
msgid "RAR主要是利用自解压等方式来构建恶意文件，同样加密的压缩包也在一定程度上可以逃逸邮件网关的检测。"
msgstr ""
"RAR files are mainly used to build malicious files through self-extracting "
"archives and similar methods. Encrypted archives can also evade email gateway"
" detection to some extent."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:30
msgid "如果前期信息收集获取到了运维等人员的邮箱，可以使用运维人员的邮箱发送，如果未收集到相关的信息，可以使用伪造发送源的方式发送邮件。"
msgstr ""
"If earlier information gathering obtained email addresses for operations staff"
" or similar personnel, those addresses can be used as senders. If no such "
"information was collected, emails can be sent with a forged sender."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:32
msgid "需要注意的是，钓鱼测试也需要注意合规问题，不能冒充监管单位、不能发送违法违规信息。具体可以参考《中华人民共和国电信条例》、《中华人民共和国互联网电子邮件服务管理办法》等法律法规。"
msgstr ""
"Phishing tests must also account for compliance requirements. Do not "
"impersonate regulatory authorities, and do not send illegal or non-compliant "
"content. For details, refer to laws and regulations such as the "
"Telecommunications Regulations of the People's Republic of China and the "
"Measures for the Administration of Internet Email Services of the People's "
"Republic of China."

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:35
msgid "其他信息"
msgstr "Other Information"

#: ../../source/info/social.rst:36
msgid "公司的公众号、企业号、网站，员工的网盘、百度文库等可能会存在一些敏感信息，如VPN/堡垒机账号、TeamViewer账号、网络设备默认口令、服务器默认口令等。"
msgstr ""
"A company's official accounts, enterprise accounts, websites, employees' "
"cloud drives, Baidu Wenku documents, and similar sources may contain "
"sensitive information such as VPN or bastion host accounts, TeamViewer "
"accounts, default passwords for network devices, and default server passwords."
